frameDefinitions: Due to chemical, nuclear, or other reactions, an Explosive explodes, potentially causing damage to the surrounding area.
An Agent causes an Explosive device to explode.
An Agent causes a Firearm to discharge, usually directing the projectile from the barrel of the Firearm (the Source), along a Path, and to a Goal.
An Agent causes a Firearm to discharge which induces the rapid motion of the Projectile.
An Earner receives Earnings by providing Goods to a Buyer; providing the Goods also generally entails a cost, which may or may not be included in the consideration.
frameExamples: The bomb <t>exploded</t> in the middle of the plaza.
The Germans wouldn't stop <t>shooting</t> cannons at them.
The bank robber <t>shot</t> at the clerks with an AK-47.
This reflects the 15 % jump in <t><fex name='Earnings'>earnings</fex></t> over 1994 .
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Explosive</fen> releases a large amount of force, destroying itself and causing damage to the surrounding area.
The location where the explosion occurs.
The <fen>Explosive</fen> causes damage to surrounding objects when operated by the <fen>Agent</fen>.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> detonates the <fen>Explosive</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Agent</fen> detonates the <fen>Explosive</fen>.
The self-directed entity that uses and activates the <fen>Firearm</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Firearm</fen> that an <fen>Agent</fen> activates so that it rapidly propels a projectile.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> fires the <fen>Firearm</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the Agent intentionally affects the Patient.
The entity whose rapid, dangerous motion is caused by the Agent and/or Firearm.
The Agent is the person performing the intentional act causing the motion of the Projectile.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the shooting event takes place.
The location in which the shooting event takes place.
The <fen>Earner</fen> is involved in a transaction or set of transactions as the party that receives payment.
<fen>Earnings</fen> are the money given to the <fen>Earner</fen> in a transaction, generally in exchange for <fen>Goods</fen>.
The time when the <fen>Earner</fen> makes their <fen>Earnings</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Earner</fen> makes their <fen>Earnings</fen>.
listRoleExamples: <fex>The bomb</fex> exploded in the middle of the plaza.
The robbers shot at the clerks <fex>as they ran out of the bank</fex>
The bankrobbers were crazy enough to shoot at the clerks with an AK-47 <fex>inside the bank</fex>
She made a lot of money <fex>in Africa</fex> .
